message.content: Yes, the authors mention that they obtained consent from the participants in their study. In the appendix section A.1, they mention that before going through the experiment, participants were asked to read and agree to a consent form, which specifies the objective and procedure of the experiment, as well as the time expected to completion and the associated reward, and finally, the risk, benefits, and confidentiality of taking part in the study.

Yes, the authors mention obtaining consent from participants in the study. They state that participants provided informed consent electronically, and the protocol was approved by the University IRB. The study was carried out in accordance with the provisions of the World Medical Association Declaration of Helsinki.

Yes, the authors discuss consent in the Appendix section A.1 (Experimental design). They mention that all participants provided informed consent electronically before going through the experiment. The consent form specifies the objective, procedure, time expected for completion, associated reward, and information about risks, benefits, and confidentiality of the study.
